  <h2>Regional Realities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access.</strong> Long gravel drives, gates and distance affect how trucks reach a tank.</li>
    <li><strong>Terrain.</strong> Plateau rock, slopes and hollows shape what is possible.</li>
    <li><strong>Layout.</strong> Where the tank and field sit matters for both service and construction.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Planning Ahead</h2>
  <p>
    Thinking about access and terrain before service or construction saves time and cost. For service coverage, see the <a href="/service-area/">Upper Cumberland service area</a>, or <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a>.
  </p>

